description: The GCM-SST encryption mode is an authenticated encryption mode.
It aims to fix problems that AES-GCM has with short tags.
While somewhat stronger than AES-GCM, Lindell and others have shown that GCM-SST is still susceptible to chosen ciphertext attacks with short tags.
The current implementation is an draft an hence may change in the future.

references.docId: Galois Counter Mode with Secure Short Tags (GCM-SST)

Basic.desc: Basic test vectors use the simplest possible inputs. These inputs often overlap with inputs from standards and RFCs. One goal of such test vectors is to simply detect distinct algorithms.

ModifiedTag.desc: The tag of this test vector has been modified. Decryption should fail.
